commit.message:
Test: use recent Minitest style

Current style has long been to use Minitest instead of MiniTest
at least for 3 years, and with minitest 5.19, MiniTest usage support is
hidden unless explicitly setting ENV["MT_COMPAT"].

https://github.com/minitest/minitest/commit/a2c6c18570f6f0a1bf6af70fe3b6d9599a13fdd6

Use Minitest and explicitly require 'minitest/unit' .
Final version
rc2 with 3.0

commit.message:
Remove rbx-2 from travis rvm config

Even though RVM still appears to support rbx-2, rbx-2 is no
longer available on travis via rvm.  It's not clear why,
I could only find this old issue which has a new report (March
this year) of the same thing:

https://github.com/rvm/rvm/issues/3617

Signed-off-by: Marc A. Paradise <marc.paradise@gmail.com>

commit.message:
Remove gemfile.lock to prevent bundler incompatibities

Bundler 2x is included in rubies version 2.6 and later,
but older rubies will still need to use bundler 1.x which
is a separate gem.

Removing the lockfile allows that to be worked out at build-time.

Signed-off-by: Marc A. Paradise <marc.paradise@gmail.com>

commit.message:
Support rubies 2.0->2.7 in win gem cross-compile

This updates the rakefile and dependencies to support
cross-compiling windows gems from 2.0 -> 2.7. This corrects a problem
in current windows installation of this gem, where ruby version > 2.3
will fail to load the extension library.

Signed-off-by: Marc A. Paradise <marc.paradise@gmail.com>
